_header: Most dear cousin of England and France
Subjects: pageant verses; occasional verse; Henry VII
_description: Pageant verses to Henry VII in A.D. 1486 at Bristol — five stanzas rhyme royal

BLCottJulBXII.First Lines:
Moost dere Cosine of england & franceKing henry the vii Noble
                    & victorious…
BLCottJulBXII.Last Lines:
…Some Remedys her in And he will quite your medeThat neuer
                    vnrewarded leveth good dede
